# PGSD kernel configuration
#
# Minimal deviation from FreeBSD GENERIC. PGSD owns the input layer
# through inputfs (per AD-1 in BACKLOG.md and the inputfs ADR series
# under inputfs/docs/adr/). To give inputfs uncontested ownership of
# HID devices, drivers that would otherwise claim USB HID children
# at boot are removed from the kernel.
#
# What stays:
#   - Everything in GENERIC by default
#   - hid     (generic HID layer, parser, descriptor handling)
#   - hidbus  (HID bus driver; inputfs attaches here per ADR 0007)
#   - usbhid  (USB-to-HID transport; required by hidbus over USB)
#
# What is removed (observed in stock GENERIC at the time of writing):
#   - hkbd    (modern HID keyboard driver, claims hidbus children)
#   - ukbd    (legacy USB keyboard driver, claims USB devices
#             directly before hidbus sees them)
#
# Anticipatory removals (drivers named in ADR 0007 that may appear
# in a future GENERIC or be loaded as modules):
#   - hms, hgame, hcons, hsctrl, utouch, hpen, hmt, hconf
#     (HID class drivers superseded by inputfs)
#   - hidmap (HID-to-evdev mapping framework; PGSD/UTF excludes
#     evdev as a structural commitment, see ADR 0001)
#
# nodevice against a driver not currently in GENERIC is harmless
# but documents intent: if any of these drivers are added to a
# future GENERIC, PGSD remains explicit about excluding them.
#
# Out of scope for this config (deliberate):
#   - evdev, uinput, EVDEV_SUPPORT remain enabled. Removing the
#     evdev userland contract is a separate architectural decision
#     with broader consequences for userland compatibility during
#     the PGSD transition period. Tracked separately, not folded
#     into AD-8.
#
# Verification target: this kernel boots, attaches inputfs to USB
# HID devices without driver competition, and passes the B.5
# bare-metal verification protocol in inputfs/docs/B5_VERIFICATION.md.

include		GENERIC

ident		PGSD

# Observed in stock GENERIC and removed:
nodevice	hkbd
nodevice	ukbd

# Anticipatory removals per ADR 0007:
nodevice	hms
nodevice	hgame
nodevice	hcons
nodevice	hsctrl
nodevice	utouch
nodevice	hpen
nodevice	hmt
nodevice	hconf
nodevice	hidmap
